    "cooking_instructions": [
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Boil a kettle, then add your <strong>basmati rice</strong>, <strong>cloves</strong>, a pinch of <strong>salt </strong>and 250ml <span class=\"text-purple\">[320ml]</span><span class=\"text-danger\"> [500ml]</span> <strong>cold water</strong> to a pot with a lid and bring to the boil over a high heat</p><p>Once boiling, reduce the heat to very low and cook, covered, for 10-12 min or until all the water has absorbed and the rice is cooked \u2013 this is your <strong>fragrant rice</strong></p><p>Once cooked, remove from the heat and keep covered</p>",
            "order": 1,
            "image": "/images/instructions/bengali-style-mustard-hake-with-fragrant-rice/step-1.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Preheat the oven to 200\u00b0C/ 180\u00b0C (fan)/ gas 6</p><p>Meanwhile, peel and finely chop (or grate) your <strong>garlic</strong></p><p>Cut your <strong>green</strong> <strong>chilli[es]</strong> in half lengthways, deseed (scrape the seeds out with a teaspoon) and chop finely</p>",
            "order": 2,
            "image": "/images/instructions/bengali-style-mustard-hake-with-fragrant-rice/step-2.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Add your <strong>wholegrain mustard</strong>, <strong>cumin seeds</strong>, <strong>yellow mustard seeds</strong>, <strong>chopped garlic</strong>, <strong>chopped chilli</strong> (can't handle the heat? Go easy!) and a generous pinch of <strong>salt</strong> to a <strong>pestle & mortar</strong> and grind to form a smooth paste</p><p>Add 2 tbsp<span class=\"text-purple\"> [3 tbsp]</span> <span class=\"text-danger\">[4 tbsp]</span> <strong>vegetable oil </strong>and mix well \u2013 this is your <strong>mustard mixture</strong></p><p>Tip: Alternatively blitz together in a food processor!</p>",
            "order": 3,
            "image": "/images/instructions/bengali-style-mustard-hake-with-fragrant-rice/step-3.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Place your <strong>creamed coconut </strong>(in its packaging!) in a mug and cover with <strong>boiled water </strong>(this softens the naturally hard cream)</p><p>Leave for 1 min, then remove from the mug</p><p>Add your <strong>ground turmeric</strong> and<strong> softened creamed coconut</strong> to the <strong>mustard mixture</strong> and give everything a good mix up \u2013 this is your <strong>Bengali-style mustard paste</strong></p>",
            "order": 4,
            "image": "/images/instructions/bengali-style-mustard-hake-with-fragrant-rice/step-4.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Cut 1 piece of <strong>baking paper</strong> (or tin foil) approx. the size of A3 sheets of paper per person</p><p>Lay each <strong>hake fillet </strong>in the middle of a piece of paper and add to a baking tray (or two!)</p><p>Spoon your <strong>Bengali-style mustard paste</strong> evenly over the hake</p><p>Scrunch the edges of the baking paper together around the hake to form a sealed parcel[s]</p>",
            "order": 5,
            "image": "/images/instructions/bengali-style-mustard-hake-with-fragrant-rice/step-5.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Put the tray[s] in the oven for 12-15 min or until the fish is cooked through \u2013 this is your <strong>Bengali-style mustard hake</strong></p><p>Tip: Your fish is cooked once it turns opaque and flakes easily</p><p>Chop your <strong>coriander</strong> finely, including the stalks</p><p>Top, tail, peel and grate your <strong>carrot[s]</strong></p>",
            "order": 6,
            "image": "/images/instructions/bengali-style-mustard-hake-with-fragrant-rice/step-6.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Wash your <strong>salad</strong>, then pat it dry with kitchen paper</p><p>Add the<strong> salad</strong>,<strong> grated carrot</strong> and <strong>chopped coriander</strong> to a bowl with the juice of <strong>half </strong>your <strong>lime[s]</strong>, a drizzle of <strong>olive oil</strong> and a generous pinch of<strong> salt</strong></p><p>Give everything a good mix up \u2013 this is your<strong> carrot & coriander salad</strong></p><p>Discard the <strong>clove[s]</strong> from the fragrant rice and cut the <strong>remaining</strong> <strong>lime</strong> into 1 wedge per person</p>",
            "order": 7,
            "image": "/images/instructions/bengali-style-mustard-hake-with-fragrant-rice/step-7.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Serve the <strong>Bengali-style mustard hake</strong> alongside the<strong> fragrant rice</strong> with the <strong>carrot & coriander salad </strong>to the side</p><p>Garnish with a <strong>lime wedge</strong></p><p>Enjoy!</p>",
            "order": 8
        }
    ],
